<section id="JWPre">
    <h2 id="BeforeStart">Before you start!</h2>
    <h3 id="GettingIn">How to get into the Convergence</h3>
    
    <p>
        The entrance for Janthir Wilds Convergences is in Lowland Shore. Go to Harvest Den waypoint <span>[&BK4OAAA=]</span>.
        The Convergence Portal is on the east side of the Bonfire Lodge (blue swirl on minimap).
    </p>
    <div id="jwentrance">
    <figure style="max-width:600px;">
        <image src="/images/JW/Shared/Lowland.png" alt="convergenceentrance" style="width:100%;max-width:600px;" />
        <figcaption>JW Convergence Entrance</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure style="max-width:300px;">
        <image src="/images/JW/Shared/LowlandWaypoint.png" alt="convergenceentrancemini" style="width:100%;" />
        <figcaption>East side of the building</figcaption>
    </figure>
    </div>
    <p>
        Public Convergences can be entered for free at designated times. Public Convergences are always normal mode.
    </p>
    <JWPublicTimes/>
    <p>
        Private Convergences can be opened whenever you want.
        To open one, it costs an <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Unstable_Rift_Motivation"><image src="https://render.guildwars2.com/file/56573075759450DD5112F1B4C7366AD85470DC2C/3187526.png" style="width:40px;"/>Unstable Rift Motivation</a>.
        Private Convergences can choose between normal or challenge mode.
        It's recommended you bring a full 50 man squad with you.
    </p>
    <h3 id="Itemstobring">Items you should bring</h3>
    <p>
        The Titans in Convergences are vulnerable to Demon Slaying items. 
        Using the Force Sigil with the Demon Slaying Sigil and Potion gives you +25% damage for the entire fight. 
        The typical power build with Force and Impact Sigils with a Sharpening Stone comes in around 10-12%, 17-19% when the foe is stunned.
    </p>
    <ul id="itemstobringul">
        <li>
            <h4>
                <image src="https://render.guildwars2.com/file/7A9EA9E0C702F8BA595973FED3A853646B2E07F8/222720.png" alt="potion of demon slaying" style="width:50px;"/>
                <a href="https://wiki.guildwars2.com/wiki/Powerful_Potion_of_Demon_Slaying">Powerful Potion of Demon Slaying</a>
            </h4>
            (1 hour): 10% Damage vs. Demons, Kryptis, and Titanspawn. -10% Damage from Demons, Kryptis, and Titanspawn.
